column42:
Legitimizing tone

This message tone allows people to feel heard and understood by validating that their feelings are normal. It means stating that it makes sense to feel the way they do or that what they are going through is very hard.  It also lets them know it’s okay to talk about their struggles with people who are close to them. This kind of support can help people feel less ashamed, less alone, and more accepted as they work through tough times. - Messages using this tone would be helpful to me
column43:
Caring/Supportive tone

This message tone focuses on building trust and showing real care. It means accepting the person without judging them, showing care about what they’re going through, and letting them know that support is available. It also means being a supportive teammate in their recovery, without pretending to know exactly how they feel. This allows the person to feel safe, accepted, and not alone. - Messages using this tone would be helpful to me
column44:
Self-Efficacy tone

This message tone allows people to feel confident using the app. It focuses on their strengths and reminds them that they have what it takes to keep going. It shows that recovery is something they can do and that using the app is a helpful, doable part of that. The goal is to make things feel possible, not overwhelming, and to let them know they have the ability to take steps forward. - Messages using this tone would be helpful to me
column45:
Acknowledging tone

This message tone is about really listening and helping someone explore their feelings without telling them what to think. It means showing care about what they’re feeling, gently offering ideas about their emotions, and repeating back what they say in a clear and caring way. This allows the person to understand their feelings better and feel supported while they figure things out. - Messages using this tone would be helpful to me
column46:
Value Affirmation tone

This message tone allows people to connect their recovery with what matters most to them. It doesn’t guess what their values are, but instead reminds them why they started this journey; like wanting to be there for family, do well at work, or feel healthier. It shows how using the app and working on recovery can support them to reach those goals and stay true to what’s important in their life. - Messages using this tone would be helpful to me
column47:
Norms tone

This message tone lets people know that others like them have used similar recovery support systems and found them useful for things like handling cravings and managing stress. By sharing that people with similar struggles have seen good results, it can build hope, a sense of connection, and a sense that others use similar systems. It reminds them that they’re part of a shared journey and that others have been successful too. - Messages using this tone would be helpful to me
column48:
Formal style

This message style will use language in a formal and professional way, as if the message came from your doctor or nurse. - Messages using this style would be helpful to me
column49:
Informal style

This message style will use language in an informal way, as if the message came from a friend. - Messages using this style would be helpful to me
